Motivation

  • Tinytest is a lightweight, no-dependency, full-featured package for unit testing
  • Testing language structure similar to testthat (expect_*)


  • Applicability for Jenkins?

  • Jenkins uses JUnit XML format to report about the test suite execution

  • Tinytest has no build in reporter for JUnit format:

    -> Tinytest2JUnit

Sources

  • git: https://scm.openanalytics.eu/git/tinytest2JUnit
  • Redmine: https://projects.openanalytics.eu/projects/tinytest2junit/
    • as subproject of “Team DST”

Testing Tinytests2JUnit

  • Different test scenarios
  • To test the package we need to use the package itself
  • master branch - test package functionality:
    • test_writeJUnit.R loops over example_tests folder
  • separate branches for special test cases:
    • see Jenkins output - tests allowed to fail

3 Ways to Run Tests in Tinytest

tinytest::test_package("mypkg", testdir = "inst/tinytest") tinytest::test_all(pkgdir = "mypkg") tinytest::run_test_dir(system.file("mypkg", package="tinytest2JUnit"))

  • test_package: test a package during R CMD check -> causes Jenkins pipeline to fail on fail of any test
  • test_all: runs tests interactively -> causes pipeline to exit on fail of any test
  • run_test_dir is the only function that stores test results without exiting Jenkins pipeline

Issues

Pipeline fails with empty test folder

Issues

Pipeline fails with empty test folder

Can be easily fixed by running:

tinytest::setup_tinytest("mypkg")

  • sets up testing framework:
    • folder in "inst/tinytest/" that contains example test file
    • add "tests/tinytest.R", which is needed to run tests during R CMD check
    • add tinytest to Suggests in DESCRIPTION file
